_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c5da.1: This is the form title 'Resident Registration Change Form' - you don't need to fill anything here as it's just the header identifying the type of form.
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c5da.2: This is a subtitle indicating the form also serves as a residence address notification - again, this is just informational text and requires no input from you.

_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:e0b42.3: Check this box if you are filing a notification for changes to late-stage elderly medical care (typically for those 75 and older). This is only relevant if the form involves elderly medical care status changes.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:e0b42.5: Check this box if you are moving into this municipality from another city/town in Japan or from abroad. This indicates you are registering as a new resident coming from outside the current jurisdiction.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:e0b42.9: This field appears to contain corrupted or unreadable characters in the image. You should refer to the original form or contact the municipal office for clarification on what should be entered here.

_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:45540.2: Check this box if you will provide your personal number (My Number). As a foreign resident with a My Number card or notification, you should typically check this box and provide your 12-digit My Number in the designated field on the form.

_vision_explanations:Addresses:9fbbff360.3: This appears to be a field for additional address information or apartment/building details. Write your apartment number, building name, or room number if applicable.
_vision_explanations:Addresses:9fbbff360.5: This field seems to be for postal code or zip code. Enter your 7-digit Japanese postal code in the format 000-0000.
_vision_explanations:Addresses:9fbbff360.12: This appears to be requesting your individual number (My Number). Enter your 12-digit individual identification number if you have been assigned one as a resident.

_vision_explanations:Addresses:d8f17afcc.9: Write the sequential number or identifier for this address entry if you have multiple addresses listed on the form. If this is your only or primary address, you can typically write '1' or leave it blank if not required.

_vision_explanations:Addresses:104a75963.10: This field asks whether you need to return any items when moving out of your current address (有 = yes, 無 = no). Most foreign residents should circle 無 (no) unless you have specific government-issued items like a senior citizen card or disability card that need to be returned to the municipal office.

_vision_explanations:Person Table:2ce640.3: Select '有' (yes) or '無' (no) to indicate whether you are moving out of the municipality. _vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.1: This is the form title - no action needed, it identifies this as a Resident Change Notification Form used when moving in Japan.
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.2: This is pre-printed text addressing the form to the Mayor of Shinjuku Ward - no action needed from you.
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.5: Check this box if you are the head of household (the main person on the residence record) filing this form yourself.
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.7: Check the appropriate box for your type of move - for example, check '転入' if moving TO this ward from another municipality.
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.9: Check this box if you are moving within the same ward/municipality (changing address but staying in Shinjuku).
_vision_explanations:Header & Dates:c431.11: Check this if you are moving into Japan from abroad or moving from another municipality - this is the most common option for foreign residents.

_vision_explanations:Person Table:749037.2: Write the sequential number for each person listed in this household registry form, starting with 1 for the first person, 2 for the second person, etc.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:749037.6: This appears to be a checkbox or field related to medical/elementary school information - leave blank unless specifically applicable to the person's educational or medical status.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:749037.15: These dots indicate continuation or additional space for writing - use this area to continue information from adjacent fields if you run out of space in the main boxes.

_vision_explanations:Person Table:5022bb.7: Write your birth year in Japanese era format (e.g., 昭和, 平成, 令和) or Western calendar year. Foreign residents can use Western calendar years if unsure of Japanese era conversions.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:5022bb.15: This appears to be a pre-printed number (22) on the form, likely indicating a section or field number - you typically don't need to write anything here as it's already filled in.

_vision_explanations:Person Table:298f79.1: These are continuation marks indicating this row continues information from a previous section or person entry. Leave blank if this is a new person entry, or fill with relevant continuation data if continuing from another page.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:298f79.11: These are continuation marks similar to field 1. Use only if you need to continue information that didn't fit in previous sections, otherwise leave blank.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:298f79.12: Check the appropriate boxes for your residence status in Japan (such as permanent resident, work visa, student visa, etc.) and other relevant status indicators. If the text appears corrupted on your form, refer to the original clean form or ask for assistance to identify the correct visa category checkboxes.

_vision_explanations:Person Table:4fdd01.2: This is a remarks/notes section where clerks or you can write any special circumstances, additional information, or comments relevant to your registration that don't fit in other fields.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:4fdd01.10: Check or mark this field if you have received and are inputting information from a moving-in notification (typically when transferring residence from another city/ward in Japan or from abroad).
_vision_explanations:Person Table:4fdd01.11: This appears to be part of a contact method or communication field - write the type of contact method being used (phone, email, etc.) in the parentheses.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:4fdd01.12: Mark this when the contact or communication process has been completed or processed successfully.
_vision_explanations:Person Table:4fdd01.13: This field indicates whether a certain time period has elapsed (likely for processing deadlines) - typically filled by municipal staff rather than residents.

_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:b7d49.1: This is an instruction telling you to fill out the form using Japanese characters (hiragana, katakana, or kanji) or Latin alphabet letters only. Avoid using other scripts like Korean hangul, Chinese simplified characters, or Arabic numerals where Japanese characters are expected.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:b7d49.2: This indicates the section is for a transfer notification (moving report) for postal mail forwarding services. You would fill this out when you want Japan Post to forward your mail from your old address to your new address.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:b7d49.3: Write the date you are submitting this form in the format year/month/day. Use the Japanese calendar year (Reiwa era) or Western calendar year as indicated on the form.
